  @{b}Welcome!@{ub}

  @{fg shine}@{" Tom's Magic WB Icons Number 5 " SYSTEM "TIGuide/Sound TIGuide/ComputerStarting.snd q"}@{fg text}                                                    2-Jan-97

  MagicWB2.0-Style Icons and other stuff in a 16 colour format.


  Don't worry if these icons look a little strange at first. Just adjust your preferences
  to a @{" 16 colour palette " LINK "16Col"}.


  Please read on on how to make your workbench compatible with the colour prefs used by many of 
  the world's greatest icon creators!


     @{" · " LINK "why"}   Not Another Set Of Magic WB Icons?!
     @{" · " LINK "icons"}   16 Colour Icons

     @{" · " SYSTEM "Multiview SCREEN Tom'sWB"}   Screen Shot 

     @{" · " LINK "Copyright"}   Copyright notice
     @{" · " LINK "Contact"}   How to reach me

     @{" · " LINK "Credits"}   Credits
@ENDNODE

@NODE "16Col" "The 16 Colour Palette"

  @{B}16 Colours on your Workbench@{UB}

  The 16 colours that I use on my Workbench are those from RomIcons9.

  This is a direct quote from RomIcons9 RI.Guide about the installation of a modified 16 colour 
  Workbench.

  Take it away Roman.

 "Steps to install my 16 colour palette on your system:

  1. Change your screenmode to 16 colors.
  2. Load the User-Startup into your editor and change the MagicWB-Daemon to:
     Run >NIL: C:MagicWB-Demon 4,123,123,123 5,175,175,175 6,170,144,124 7,255,169,151 8,0,0,255 9,50,50,50 10,96,128,96 11,226,209,119 
12,255,212,203 13,122,96,72 14,210,210,210 15,229,93,93
  3. Do the same with your Startup-Sequence
  4. Load Prefs/Palette and change the last four colours to
            255,212,203   122,96,72   210,210,210   229,93,93
     and save it. After re-boot everything should work fine."

  There you have it all the instructions you need to make your MWB2.0 look really @{" Cool " SYSTEM "TIGuide/SOUND TIGuide/ComputerHacking.snd q"} too!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "why" "Not Another Set Of Magic WB Icons |-O"

  @{B}Does The World Need Another Set Of Icons?@{UB}

  I think I answered this question in my last release. However, after the release of my latest
  WB ScreenGrab (TomsWB.lha [Aminet:pix/wb]) I received quite a few e-mails wanting to know how
  I did it and where they could get the icons to spruce up their Workbench. So I decided to
  release another TomIcons which includes many of my new and revamped icons. If you like them
  why not tell @{" Me " LINK "Contact"}.

  One e-mail that I did receive was from Olaf Groener. He initially wanted my Tool Manager
  dock template and a few days later a bunch of Tool Manager docks in my style arrived in 
  the mail. They are included here in The Extra Bonus drawer and Olaf can be contacted at
  the e-mail address shown below his drawer icon.
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "icons" "TomIcons4 Information"

  @{b}16 Colour Icons@{ub}

  Hi Everyone :-)!

  Here is my fifth collection of MWB Icons and other stuff that I have drawn or created over the 
  last several months. Most of them require the modified 16 colour palette discussed in @{" RomIcons9 " SYSTEM "TIGuide/Sound TIGuide/Roadrunner.snd q"}.
  @{" Click Here " LINK "16Col"} for further details.

  I am not an artist but use a registered version of Iconian and Picticon to cut and paste 
  images to produce the icons that are on your screen now. Once in a while Personal Paint 6.3 
  came in handy as well ;-).

    @{" Click Here " SYSTEM "Multiview SCREEN Tom'sWB"} for a brief look at my Workbench Screen.

  As you can see I have abandoned the use of Tool Manager in favour of John Corigliano's
  StartMenu 2.0 TaskBar programme. I find it takes up less ChipRam to use and is acceptably
  quick enough for my needs. I have included some icons and brushes to compliment this great
  little programme. My settings for StartMenu are @{" Here " SYSTEM "Multiview TIGuide/StartMenu.iff"}
					      and @{" Here " SYSTEM "Multiview TIGuide/StartMenu2.iff"}.

 

 
@ENDNODE

